Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer parameter `n` must be equal to the length of the integer array parameter `nums`.
- The integer parameter `left` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to `n * (n + 1) / 2`.
- The integer parameter `right` must be greater than or equal to `left` and less than or equal to `n * (n + 1) / 2`.
- The integer result is the sum of the numbers from index `left` to index `right`, inclusive, in the new array created from the sorted non-empty continuous subarray sums of the integer array parameter `nums`.
- The integer result must be modulo 10^9 + 7.